\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes. Yes. I used to love washing. And I used to get the job of washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Any other jobs you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh - the cooking and - and general cleaning all through. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 So you and your sisters really helped with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 The - me elder sister
 died - in 19 - oh now wait a minute, 1918. Yes. The eldest one. And - then Frances - used to sort of take over. And - when she got a job she - got fed up with being at home I think and - she got a job - in London, working for Lord and Lady Lindsey. And t
hen - she came home after couple of years there and - and went back again with Lord Holland and his family. Oh she moved around, yes. 'Course then I was then the eldest at me then. Used to have to do the lot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 After you left school did you carry on helping in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 When you were at Marton Road was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Most of it was done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did your mother pay anyone to help there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 We used to have an old lady used to come in, and she used to help with the general cleaning like. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What hours did she work, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh she would come any time. Yes. Just when she felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did she come in each day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes, practically each day, she'd - perhaps come - about ten o'clock on a morning and then she'd decide she'd have to go home about three.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did she ever look after the children at all? You'd be older then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes. There was only Isabelle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 So she didn't have anything to do with you really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh very well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 She was a dear old soul. What did she call us?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What did she call you and your mother, how did she address you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh just - ordinary you know, our own names. Yes. Always Missus to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What did you call her, do you remember?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Mary Ann. She was a really Mary Ann and all. Aye, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Your sisters had the same sort of jobs to do then until they left, just helping in the house generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 
Did the older children help the younger ever at all with things they found difficult, such as dressing or eating or look after them in other ways, did your older sisters look after you or Isabelle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well - no, I don't re
member them really doing much. Me mother did more when we were little and then could - we could look after ourselves after that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did the younger children ever help the older ones in any ways, did Isabelle and you ever to anything for Frances 
and Annie, any particular jobs you had to do for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 No. Not very particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well we used to always have to be in bed by half past nine. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 No, more or less put ourselves to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What age would you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well the usual - we always had to be in - you know, in bed by about half past nine to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What age would it be when you started to put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh I should - when we went to live in Marton Road, about eight year old. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Before that was it your mother that put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone, at the first house you'd have to wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 So who did you share the bedroom with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well the - the four of us - all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 How did you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Two separate beds. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Two in each bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did your mother and father have the other bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes, they had the other room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What room did you bath in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh downstairs in the kitchen. In the bath in front of the fire. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well it all depended, if we were - got very dirty well 
it was - two or three times a week. But if not it was - you know, if we kept pretty clean well it was once a week. It was the effort of dragging the bath out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 When did you have clean clothes to put on, was that any special time of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh any time we needed them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 When you went to the house at Marton Road how many rooms were there, you must have had a lot if there were four bedrooms to let off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes. How big was it? There was - four - one - one, two, three, four, five, six -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Six bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes, and - then there was like front sitting room, back sitting room and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Was there a bathroom in that one or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did you still share a bedroom with your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Where did the family have their meals at Fallows Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Very seldom. 'Cos the other room was only tiny, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 In the little kitchenette, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What sort of cooking equipment did she have, did she have gas or a range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Gas stove. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Do you remember what time breakfast was eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh I should imagine - I don't exactly know but - I should imagine around half past eight-ish, on account of school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Which members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 My father used to have his early. Yes, he - he used to go out to work at - six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Would he get his own breakfast or did your mother get up for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Oh no, he got his own breakfast. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 But the rest of you had it about half past eight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What did you usually have to eat and drink for your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well - I couldn't exactly say, I - I don't remember that far how much we had to eat but I - I know we used to have a lot of - fr}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1182045\charrsid5856546 ying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 
 bread, me mother used to do a lot of - beef and that you know and always have dripping. Lovely dripping and - we used to often have dripping and bread but it - whether we had it for breakfast, I - I 
- I don't know. I And another thing we used to often have was - scrambled eggs - on toast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1182045\charrsid5856546 Would that be for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546  breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 It could have been, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What would you drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Do you know what hour father had for his breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 He'd have a bit of bacon or anything that was going. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Would he drink tea as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Was breakfast on Sundays any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Well we were all more or less together then on a Sunday, and - and we all - I think
 I remember then we used to have bacon and egg and - suchlike. Yes. You had more time to - get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 When did you have your main meal, was that in the middle of the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Who would be present for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 All of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Did your father come in for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5314155 DR  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 Yes. We used to always wait for him. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10687487 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4684011\charrsid5856546 What time would that be?
